{
  "stem": "11133.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think it was just a general fear, and is-- was our life going to change?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and a feeling of-- we couldn't do certain things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then when war broke out, of course, right away, the schools were closed, and so our lives really changed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think as soon as-- as soon as war broke out, you know, and we heard-- well, bombs started falling-- there were like three, I think, fell in Krakow on the radio station.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had just received, just prior to that, a puppy, which was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My-- my aunt bought it for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a little spitz, white spitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one of the first things that I had to part with, painfully, was to give up my dog to a shelter, because my parents felt that, couldn't take care of it with the war approaching.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I distinctly remember having to take him to a shelter.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was painful, because I didn't understand why, you know-- I was only about eight years old at the time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember people panicking.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a general fear.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember that the neighbors that discussed the impending problems in the courtyard on the 2nd of September-- I mean, war started on the 1st September-- on the 2nd of September, appeared with armbands sporting swastikas.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They turned out to have been fifth columnists.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was really kind of an incredible feeling to realize that you've been trusting people and-- an telling them your feelings and your attitudes, and they were sympathizers of the Nazis, or of the Germans at the time, you know.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think we really fully realized what Nazism was till it hit us later.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that time, we just talked about Germany invading Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
